ck library metadata and not user code. I need to figure out if this includes test class methods accessed by Spring Boot.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying metadata and class naming**\\n\\nI'm thinking about how metadata for test classes might be generated during the build process, not necessarily among the resources. The native image compiles tests with their respective classes, so the configuration can include methods effectively. It’s important to avoid using \\\"$\\\" in test class or file names.\\n\\nI wonder if I can get around using inner classes by adding a top-level non-public class that doesn't use \\\"$\\\". So, having a package-private final class like ClearableCacheClassLoader in the same Java file would work better and maintain a single mapping without using \\\"$\\\".\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating method access and class visibility**\\n\\nI'm considering if I need to use `AtomicBoolean` for thread safety in my classloader. Since it might be called on the same thread, a simple boolean is probably fine, and I can assert after the finally block. \\n\\nI’m wondering if a package-private method would be an issue, especially if the ClassLoader constructor is protected. If I getDeclaredMethod for \\\"clearCache\\\" in a package-private class, will it work? I should make the method public. But if the class is package-private, the method can still be public but inaccessible from `org.springframework.boot`.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_nKqbihgIz3NsQ3pAKkKYsbJ7|fc_0790cd05e76bd8fe016a0132884678819d9553fb65424330cf", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot/2.6.3/src/test/java/org_springframework_boot/spring_boot/ClearCachesApplicationListenerTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_springframework_boot.spring_boot;\n\nimport java.util.Optional;\n\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport org.springframework.boot.Banner;\nimport org.springframework.boot.SpringApplication;\nimport org.springframework.context.ApplicationListener;\nimport org.springframework.context.event.ContextRefreshedEvent;\nimport org.springframework.context.support.GenericApplicationContext;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class ClearCachesApplicationListenerTest {\n\n    @Test\n    void clearsContextClassLoaderCacheWhenContextIsRefreshed() {\n        CacheClearingClassLoader cacheClearingClassLoader = new CacheClearingClassLoader(\n                Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader());\n        ClassLoader previousClassLoader = Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader();\n        ApplicationListener<ContextRefreshedEvent> listener = getClearCachesApplicationListener();\n        try (GenericApplicationContext context = new GenericApplicationContext()) {\n            Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(cacheClearingClassLoader);\n\n            listener.onApplicationEvent(new ContextRefreshedEvent(context));\n        }\n        finally {\n            Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(previousClassLoader);\n        }\n\n        assertThat(cacheClearingClassLoader.isCacheCleared()).isTrue();\n    }\n\n    private static ApplicationListener<ContextRefreshedEvent> getClearCachesApplicationListener() {\n        SpringApplication application = new SpringApplication(TestApplication.class);\n        application.setBannerMode(Banner.Mode.OFF);\n        Optional<ApplicationListener<?>> listener = application.getListeners().stream()\n                .filter((candidate) -> candidate.getClass().getName()\n                        .equals(\"org.springframework.boot.ClearCachesApplicationListener\"))\n                .findFirst();\n        assertThat(listener).isPresent();\n        return asContextRefreshedEventListener(listener.get());\n    }\n\n    @SuppressWarnings(\"unchecked\")\n    private static ApplicationListener<ContextRefreshedEvent> asContextRefreshedEventListener(\n            ApplicationListener<?> listener) {\n        return (ApplicationListener<ContextRefreshedEvent>) listener;\n    }\n\n    public static final class TestApplication {\n\n        public TestApplication() {\n        }\n\n    }\n\n    public static final class CacheClearingClassLoader extends ClassLoader {\n\n        private boolean cacheCleared;\n\n        CacheClearingClassLoader(ClassLoader parent) {\n            super(parent);\n        }\n\n        public void clearCache() {\n            this.cacheCleared = true;\n        }\n\n        boolean isCacheCleared() {\n            return this.cacheCleared;\n        }\n\n    }\n\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 648, "output": 1547, "cacheRead": 16896, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 19091, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778463354596, "responseId": "resp_0790cd05e76bd8fe016a01327b3030819d815349819ae62a06"}}
[tool-exec] start id=call_nKqbihgIz3NsQ3pAKkKYsbJ7|fc_0790cd05e76bd8fe016a0132884678819d9553fb65424330cf name=write args={"path": "tests/src/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot/2.6.3/src/test/java/org_springframework_boot/spring_boot/ClearCachesApplicationListenerTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_springframework_boot.spring_boot;\n\nimport java.util.Optional;\n\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport org.springframework.boot.Banner;\nimport org.springframework.boot.SpringApplication;\nimport org.springframework.context.ApplicationListener;\nimport org.springframework.context.event.ContextRefreshedEvent;\nimport org.springframework.context.support.GenericApplicationContext;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class ClearCachesApplicationListenerTest {\n\n    @Test\n    void clearsContextClassLoaderCacheWhenContextIsRefreshed() {\n        CacheClearingClassLoader cacheClearingClassLoader = new CacheClearingClassLoader(\n                Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader());\n        ClassLoader previousClassLoader = Thread.currentThread().getContextClassLoader();\n        ApplicationListener<ContextRefreshedEvent> listener = getClearCachesApplicationListener();\n        try (GenericApplicationContext context = new GenericApplicationContext()) {\n            Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(cacheClearingClassLoader);\n\n            listener.onApplicationEvent(new ContextRefreshedEvent(context));\n        }\n        finally {\n            Thread.currentThread().setContextClassLoader(previousClassLoader);\n        }\n\n        assertThat(cacheClearingClassLoader.isCacheCleared()).isTrue();\n    }\n\n    private static ApplicationListener<ContextRefreshedEvent> getClearCachesApplicationListener() {\n        SpringApplication application = new SpringApplication(TestApplication.class);\n        application.setBannerMode(Banner.Mode.OFF);\n        Optional<ApplicationListener<?>> listener = application.getListeners().stream()\n                .filter((candidate) -> candidate.getClass().getName()\n                        .equals(\"org.springframework.boot.ClearCachesApplicationListener\"))\n                .findFirst();\n        assertThat(listener).isPresent();\n        return asContextRefreshedEventListener(listener.get());\n    }\n\n    @SuppressWarnings(\"unchecked\")\n    private static ApplicationListener<ContextRefreshedEvent> asContextRefreshedEventListener(\n            ApplicationListener<?> listener) {\n        return (ApplicationListener<ContextRefreshedEvent>) listener;\n    }\n\n    public static final class TestApplication {\n\n        public TestApplication() {\n        }\n\n    }\n\n    public static final class CacheClearingClassLoader extends ClassLoader {\n\n        private boolean cacheCleared;\n\n        CacheClearingClassLoader(ClassLoader parent) {\n            super(parent);\n        }\n\n        public void clearCache() {\n            this.cacheCleared = true;\n        }\n\n        boolean isCacheCleared() {\n            return this.cacheCleared;\n        }\n\n    }\n\n}\n"}
